02:07.504 --> 02:10.691
<i>♪ Bluesy vocalizing ♪</i>

02:10.779 --> 02:14.708
<i>- ♪ Lord My time
- Lord my time ♪</i>

02:14.796 --> 02:16.238
<i>♪ Oh Lord ♪</i>

02:16.326 --> 02:18.675
<i>♪ Goin' home ♪</i>

02:18.763 --> 02:20.613
<i>♪ Oh Lord ♪</i>

02:20.701 --> 02:22.495
<i>♪ Goin' home, Lord ♪</i>

02:22.583 --> 02:23.871
<i>♪ I'm home ♪</i>

02:23.959 --> 02:26.048
<i>♪ She goin' home ♪</i>

02:26.136 --> 02:27.863
<i>♪ Make me feel like ♪</i>

02:27.951 --> 02:30.134
<i>♪ Make me
feel like ♪</i>

02:30.374 --> 02:31.691
<i>♪ My time ♪</i>

02:31.816 --> 02:33.174
♪ Lord My time ♪

02:33.262 --> 02:34.253
<i>♪ Goin' home ♪</i>

02:34.341 --> 02:36.825
<i>♪ Ooh ooh‐ooh‐ooh ♪</i>

02:38.458 --> 02:40.762
<i>‐ ♪ Mmm ♪</i>
‐ Why me?

02:40.895 --> 02:42.458
Why did I survive?

02:43.841 --> 02:45.940
It was pretty
spectacular, Ray.

02:46.106 --> 02:47.341
I'm talkin'...

02:47.539 --> 02:49.669
genuine hand of God here...

02:49.871 --> 02:51.786
I think...

02:52.414 --> 02:54.145
I may be blessed.

02:57.356 --> 02:59.137
You don't wanna know
what happened?

02:59.478 --> 03:00.653
No.

03:01.970 --> 03:03.598
Not even curious?

03:07.081 --> 03:09.731
You know, you live through
somethin' like that, and...

03:09.925 --> 03:11.987
it gets you thinkin'
about

03:12.075 --> 03:13.676
what's really important...

03:14.293 --> 03:16.653
our purpose here,
shit like that.

03:22.224 --> 03:23.817
Where we goin', Ray?

03:24.833 --> 03:26.676
Those cops you chopped up...

03:28.169 --> 03:29.622
one of the heads came up.

03:30.321 --> 03:31.755
Jesus.

03:34.247 --> 03:35.653
What are you gonna do?

03:35.741 --> 03:38.020
Gonna make it easy
for them to pin it on you.

03:38.277 --> 03:40.098
I'm not going back
to prison.

03:40.296 --> 03:42.048
I can't go back, Ray.

03:42.319 --> 03:43.674
Course you can't.

03:43.762 --> 03:45.130
You're dead.

04:01.625 --> 04:04.231
That was a nice urn
you bought for me.

04:05.081 --> 04:07.661
I'm not sure about the...
Eternal Flame thing.

04:07.749 --> 04:09.630
I didn't know
they made those.

04:10.229 --> 04:12.583
Kind of a strange...

04:13.059 --> 04:16.208
strange choice, actually,
for a guy who burned to death.

04:23.394 --> 04:25.395
You can admit
you were sad, Ray,

04:25.498 --> 04:28.488
when you heard that I was dead.
It's only natural.

04:28.887 --> 04:29.932
‐ What?

04:30.020 --> 04:31.466
‐ Nothing to be ashamed of.

04:31.591 --> 04:33.208
No one would judge ya
for it

04:33.296 --> 04:35.481
if you shed a tear or two
for your old man.

05:06.387 --> 05:08.966
I want you to stand there,
put your prints on the door.

05:09.451 --> 05:12.037
Sure... yeah.

05:13.724 --> 05:15.356
I'm puttin' 'em
everywhere here.

05:22.324 --> 05:24.660
He was right here
when I popped him.

05:26.375 --> 05:27.747
What?

05:28.264 --> 05:31.551
The cop I shot, when I saved
your life, Raymond.

05:32.123 --> 05:33.249
Here.

05:33.715 --> 05:35.098
Blow your nose.

05:36.070 --> 05:38.880
Sure... my blood.

05:42.169 --> 05:44.028
Ooh, that's a lotta DNA.

05:45.268 --> 05:46.864
Have a party.

06:28.129 --> 06:29.906
So why didn't I
go up in flames?

06:30.022 --> 06:31.883
It was like the <i>Titanic.</i>

06:32.406 --> 06:34.125
Remember in the <i>Titantic</i>

06:34.766 --> 06:38.896
where... the rear of the boat
goes up in the air

06:38.984 --> 06:40.992
and everyone else
is drowning?

06:41.277 --> 06:44.203
It's the same thing
because the back of the bus...

06:44.651 --> 06:47.414
sorta catches all the bumps
the hardest.

06:47.570 --> 06:49.937
So the security door
just opened right up

06:50.591 --> 06:51.779
like the Red Sea partin'.

06:52.218 --> 06:54.258
And I'm out the fuckin' door.

06:58.943 --> 07:00.789
Shoulda seen the explosion,
Ray, and the...

07:01.052 --> 07:02.484
flames.

07:02.729 --> 07:06.234
And me flyin' through the air
out the back of the bus...

07:06.376 --> 07:09.337
carried on angel wings
or something.

07:09.729 --> 07:11.189
What kinda boat did you take?

07:11.437 --> 07:13.008
One‐a those little
Whalers out there.

07:13.828 --> 07:15.672
Wasn't normal, Ray.

07:16.132 --> 07:18.492
Was from somethin' else,
ya know?

07:19.648 --> 07:20.983
Sign this.

07:35.050 --> 07:36.531
The fuck is that?

07:37.168 --> 07:39.078
They'll match up
the handwritin'.

07:39.955 --> 07:41.531
Bein' a cop killer's
one thing, Ray,

07:41.619 --> 07:43.454
but don't make me look
stupid.

07:53.820 --> 07:55.164
Ah, yeah.

07:55.393 --> 07:58.472
You popped seven rounds
into a guy just sittin' down.

07:58.735 --> 08:00.339
Put your prints
on this.

08:00.778 --> 08:02.768
Didn't wanna give him
a chance, did ya?

08:07.452 --> 08:09.095
‐ Let's go.
‐ Wait a minute.

08:09.308 --> 08:10.581
What?

08:11.826 --> 08:13.940
I would never get rid
of a gun

08:14.101 --> 08:15.964
and not wipe it down.

08:17.222 --> 08:18.598
But...

08:20.674 --> 08:23.081
Under the duress of a murder,

08:23.457 --> 08:25.636
I might accidentally...

08:26.083 --> 08:27.793
leave a new print

08:28.203 --> 08:30.143
as I'm wipin' down the old.

08:31.509 --> 08:32.729
You're welcome.

08:36.485 --> 08:39.110
Jesus fuckin' Christ.

08:54.563 --> 08:55.766
The <i>Post.</i>

08:56.805 --> 09:00.851
[♪♪♪]

09:14.422 --> 09:16.665
‐ Ma!
‐ Oh, my baby.

09:17.079 --> 09:18.548
Hi.

09:19.343 --> 09:22.221
‐ I missed you.
‐ Oh, my sweetheart.

09:22.309 --> 09:23.893
Let me look at you.

09:24.883 --> 09:26.031
Been a long time, huh?

09:26.114 --> 09:27.438
Mm‐hmm.

09:28.539 --> 09:30.391
Sorry about Mickey.

09:33.197 --> 09:34.758
About that...

09:47.462 --> 09:48.704
What is this?

09:48.862 --> 09:50.446
The story's
changed.

09:51.094 --> 09:52.223
Okay...

09:52.307 --> 09:54.141
My father killed everyone.

09:55.690 --> 09:57.191
Pleasure to meet you.

09:57.479 --> 09:58.844
You have lovely eyes.

09:59.276 --> 10:02.779
This is the guy Mac told you
killed Rad, Al, and Bianchi.

10:04.258 --> 10:05.501
Him?

10:05.680 --> 10:08.454
You're not exactly
meeting me at my best, darling.

10:08.718 --> 10:10.719
Where's that leave Mac
in all this?

10:10.968 --> 10:12.595
He's not a cop killer.

10:23.102 --> 10:24.946
That was a kindness
you did, Raymond.

10:25.034 --> 10:27.298
A <i>mitzvah,</i> like the Jewish
people call it.

10:27.501 --> 10:28.571
What?

10:28.743 --> 10:30.579
Supportin' the widow.

10:31.497 --> 10:33.852
That's the fuckin' purpose
I'm talkin' about.

10:42.462 --> 10:43.602
Hi, Ray.

10:43.690 --> 10:45.999
Make the calls.
Destroy the phones.

10:46.087 --> 10:47.133
Is that Sandy?

10:47.221 --> 10:48.552
You don't have ta
tell me that.

10:48.640 --> 10:50.183
I'm not a fuckin' amateur.

10:52.295 --> 10:53.473
Let me talk to her.

10:54.216 --> 10:57.290
You're dead.
You don't talk to anyone.

11:21.982 --> 11:24.691
Hello, is this the tip line?

11:24.829 --> 11:26.552
‐ <i>Yes, it is.</i>
‐ Good.

11:26.890 --> 11:30.841
Listen, uh... I was
pickin' up trash today

11:30.955 --> 11:32.880
in an alley behind, uh,

11:32.974 --> 11:35.841
272 Altoona Street.

11:36.177 --> 11:38.621
I like to volunteer

11:38.841 --> 11:40.864
and beautify the neighborhood.

11:41.279 --> 11:44.614
And I found something
very strange...

11:44.863 --> 11:46.872
a bloodied shirt and a gun.

11:47.005 --> 11:48.919
<i>A bloody shirt and gun.
And what was your name?</i>

11:49.007 --> 11:53.595
Uh, no, dear, I, uh,
I will not leave my name.

11:54.100 --> 11:56.300
Uh... the <i>Bible</i> tells us

11:56.388 --> 11:59.098
never to practice
our good deeds in public

11:59.454 --> 12:04.200
or we'll have no reward
from our Father in heaven.

12:14.946 --> 12:16.364
I mean, I'm not saying
I'm vain...

12:16.459 --> 12:18.536
Uh‐huh.

12:22.997 --> 12:24.250
Daryll Donovan.

12:25.207 --> 12:26.168
Yeah, what's up?

12:26.290 --> 12:28.485
Detective Perry.
NYPD.

12:30.126 --> 12:31.147
I have some questions

12:31.235 --> 12:33.118
about the night
of November seventh.

12:33.551 --> 12:35.134
November seventh?

12:35.950 --> 12:37.431
What, like last year
November seventh?

12:37.519 --> 12:39.104
You remember where
you were that night?

12:39.192 --> 12:40.673
Ah... yes.

12:40.877 --> 12:43.040
I do, um, I went to...

12:43.136 --> 12:45.087
Madison Square Garden
for the first time.

12:45.266 --> 12:46.415
The J. W. H. show.

12:46.503 --> 12:48.130
J.W.H. show.

12:48.524 --> 12:50.134
Jonathan Walker Hanson.

12:50.369 --> 12:51.923
And, oh, yes,
he killed it.

12:52.018 --> 12:54.103
He must be thrilled
with the new demographic.

12:54.868 --> 12:56.157
What?

12:56.501 --> 12:58.540
Can anyone else
confirm you being there?

12:58.667 --> 13:01.272
Yeah, my, um, I went with
my brother and my niece

13:01.360 --> 13:02.405
and her husband.

13:02.493 --> 13:04.446
- ‐ Your family; of course.
- ‐ Yeah.

13:04.534 --> 13:07.257
Oh, and, uh, you know,
we got to go backstage

13:07.345 --> 13:09.389
and, like, meet
Jonathan Walker Hanson.

13:09.477 --> 13:12.382
And, uh, we also met his, uh,
producer Adam Rain.

13:12.652 --> 13:13.891
I ask them about you,

13:13.979 --> 13:15.380
‐ they'll remember?
‐ I don't know,

13:15.468 --> 13:17.430
I mean... I mean,
we had a good talk, though.

13:17.518 --> 13:19.751
We talked about, like,
you know, baseball,

13:19.889 --> 13:21.641
like the Dodgers, Yankees,
who's better.

13:21.729 --> 13:23.407
Oh, he, yeah, he likes dogs.

13:23.555 --> 13:26.399
‐ Who?
‐ Jonathan Walker Hanson.

13:26.487 --> 13:27.529
I said that already.

13:27.647 --> 13:29.751
I need receipts,
ticket stubs,

13:29.839 --> 13:32.055
selfies of you backstage
with those dogs.

13:32.143 --> 13:35.258
Otherwise, next time,
I'm gonna have to take you in.

13:36.821 --> 13:38.290
Okay.

13:38.790 --> 13:40.501
Have a good day.

13:44.868 --> 13:48.251
Okay, so what was <i>that</i>
all about?

13:48.504 --> 13:49.812
Ma, I dunno!

13:49.941 --> 13:50.962
Mm‐hmm.

13:51.050 --> 13:54.649
Well, it sounds like
some Donovan bull‐shit to me.

13:55.508 --> 13:57.235
Ma, don't worry about it,
all right?

13:57.323 --> 13:58.758
We good!

13:58.946 --> 14:00.610
Daryll...

14:01.230 --> 14:03.837
you gonna land your ass
in prison.

14:05.249 --> 14:06.618
Shit!

14:16.738 --> 14:18.446
‐ Is this the tip line?
‐ <i>Yes, ma'am.</i>

14:18.534 --> 14:21.454
Ah... so listen, uh...

14:21.628 --> 14:26.001
I was suckin' off one‐a
my Johns the other day and...

14:26.089 --> 14:30.260
he runs a boat rental outfit
over there on Long Island.

14:30.348 --> 14:31.725
<i>North Shore or South Shore?</i>

14:31.813 --> 14:34.941
Yeah, right near where all
those heads is comin' up.

14:35.117 --> 14:36.368
<i>So, Huntington?</i>

14:36.844 --> 14:38.509
Yeah, that's right.

14:38.593 --> 14:40.204
<i>And which rental
store in Huntington?</i>

14:40.292 --> 14:41.803
- ‐ Uh‐huh.
- ‐ <i>No, whi...</i>

14:41.891 --> 14:42.972
You got it.

15:02.912 --> 15:04.212
Terry.

15:06.396 --> 15:07.743
You came back.

15:08.672 --> 15:10.399
Yeah, I‐I did.

15:11.292 --> 15:14.102
I... I wanna do it
again.

15:16.970 --> 15:18.446
Come on.

15:27.118 --> 15:28.219
<i>A raise?</i>

15:28.307 --> 15:30.547
‐ Yeah.
‐ A raise.

15:31.919 --> 15:34.547
I protected the store,
right, I saved lives.

15:34.658 --> 15:37.084
What you did, Brendan...
firing a weapon,

15:37.172 --> 15:40.712
injuring two people...
that is not our safety policy.

15:40.912 --> 15:42.712
Well, fuck your safety policy,
all right?

15:42.956 --> 15:44.305
Those gunmen...

15:44.393 --> 15:45.724
Gunmen?

15:46.032 --> 15:47.899
You shot a teenager
in the back...

15:48.018 --> 15:49.868
who now is in intensive care.

15:50.449 --> 15:53.355
‐ Intensive care?
‐ And God forbid if he dies,

15:53.443 --> 15:55.695
you'll be getting whatever's
the opposite of a raise.

15:56.293 --> 15:58.377
<i>Lawyers and corporate
are coming in later today</i>

15:58.465 --> 16:01.416
<i>to decide whether we're
defending you, firing you,</i>

16:01.504 --> 16:02.746
<i>or suing you,</i>

16:02.834 --> 16:04.088
<i>and you want a raise.</i>

16:04.573 --> 16:06.973
<i>Read your contract...</i>

16:17.613 --> 16:18.642
Yeah.

16:18.730 --> 16:20.215
<i>That little person.</i>

16:20.598 --> 16:21.723
What?

16:21.872 --> 16:23.676
<i>The picture
of the little person.</i>

16:23.997 --> 16:26.254
‐ What about him?
<i>‐ He won't talk, will he?</i>

16:26.502 --> 16:29.402
‐ No.
<i>‐ Good. That's good.</i>

16:29.836 --> 16:31.838
The D. A.'s gonna file charges
against Sullivan...

16:31.962 --> 16:34.520
child endangerment,
sex crimes.

16:36.830 --> 16:39.043
I want you to find me
a ten‐year‐old boy.

16:39.472 --> 16:41.387
‐ What for?
<i>‐ To say he was the kid</i>

16:41.475 --> 16:42.949
<i>in the picture.</i>

16:44.510 --> 16:45.988
I want you to do that.

16:49.718 --> 16:51.004
Trouble?

16:59.102 --> 17:01.543
The Fortress
of Solitude, huh?

17:06.039 --> 17:08.541
What's, uh, what's with
all the tequila?

17:09.152 --> 17:10.478
It's Tommy Wheeler's
place.

17:10.566 --> 17:12.559
We're just usin'
the back for a while.

17:15.458 --> 17:16.541
You could put the Raiders

17:16.626 --> 17:18.269
of the fuckin'
Lost Ark in here.

17:18.451 --> 17:19.618
Hey, guys.

17:21.549 --> 17:23.596
‐ You got everything?
‐ Yeah, the money and ticket

17:23.684 --> 17:25.560
are ready... just give me
a second with the passport.

17:25.646 --> 17:27.394
Hey, Smitty, man.

17:28.058 --> 17:29.379
You all right?

17:29.496 --> 17:30.957
I'm fuckin' here.

17:32.642 --> 17:34.027
Back from the dead.

17:34.115 --> 17:35.894
Like the Son of God risen up.

17:36.840 --> 17:38.637
Adam Rain sent you that.

17:44.228 --> 17:46.564
I was in the bus
with everyone else,

17:47.054 --> 17:49.963
and I‐I'm... workin' on
these cuffs that were tight

17:50.051 --> 17:51.324
and I'm tryin'
to loosen 'em.

17:51.412 --> 17:53.706
And I checked
my, uh, four‐leaf clover.

17:53.794 --> 17:55.921
See?
Got a four‐leaf clover there.

17:56.152 --> 17:57.324
Luck o' the Irish.

17:57.412 --> 17:59.691
Does, uh... he know
he's goin'?

18:00.926 --> 18:02.176
Not yet.

18:04.246 --> 18:05.258
‐ Puhhh... puuuhhhh...
‐ Hey, Ray.

18:05.341 --> 18:07.152
Have you...
have you heard this story?

18:07.595 --> 18:08.730
Yeah, I heard it.

18:08.818 --> 18:10.904
‐ It's fuckin' amazing, it's...
‐ Yeah, and I...

18:11.006 --> 18:12.257
I musta gone out.

18:12.364 --> 18:15.129
I musta gone out
for a second or two.

18:21.598 --> 18:23.613
So where're we goin'?

18:23.823 --> 18:25.840
To see the shaman.

18:27.428 --> 18:28.902
W‐what does he do?

18:29.183 --> 18:30.668
Parkinson's.

18:31.520 --> 18:33.582
Cancer, Alzheimer's,

18:33.744 --> 18:35.723
autism, manic depression.

18:36.015 --> 18:38.402
It's all just blocked
channels in the body.

18:38.743 --> 18:40.660
You shove western medicine
into those channels,

18:40.748 --> 18:43.584
and that pharmaceutical poison
just blocks 'em even more.

18:43.705 --> 18:45.525
But what the shaman does

18:45.613 --> 18:48.465
is he asks you to clear
those channels.

18:49.213 --> 18:50.465
So...

18:50.587 --> 18:52.238
this guy c...

18:52.683 --> 18:54.393
can cure me?

18:54.734 --> 18:58.316
He is going to show you
a way to cure yourself.

19:02.535 --> 19:06.035
I see nothin' but red,
smoke, and fuckin' flames

19:06.140 --> 19:08.074
and a little flicker
off to the side,

19:08.162 --> 19:09.455
and it's burnin' metal.

19:09.681 --> 19:10.932
And I...

19:11.020 --> 19:13.105
Uh...
can I help you?

19:13.374 --> 19:15.056
I need to speak with
Ray Donovan.

19:15.144 --> 19:16.302
Uh, do you have
an appointment?

19:16.389 --> 19:19.418
Just... tell him that
Kevin Sullivan's sister's here.

19:25.225 --> 19:26.324
Sullivan.

19:26.904 --> 19:28.655
You got people in Boston?

19:30.385 --> 19:31.480
I do...

19:31.568 --> 19:33.027
Mr. Wallace.

19:34.148 --> 19:37.285
Mr. Wallace, right this way.

19:40.066 --> 19:43.176
Oh! Oh, yes, dear.

19:55.346 --> 19:57.637
Can we speak privately?

19:58.274 --> 19:59.613
Sure.

20:10.589 --> 20:12.699
Is that Jim Sullivan's
daughter?

20:14.670 --> 20:15.879
I‐I don't know.

20:15.971 --> 20:17.371
Grew into a beauty.

20:17.661 --> 20:19.637
Seems nice enough, too,
which is a miracle,

20:19.725 --> 20:22.426
considering her father's
a legitimate piece of shit.

20:22.621 --> 20:23.887
Have a seat.

20:24.699 --> 20:26.691
I found something
that I wanted to give you.

20:26.774 --> 20:27.926
Yeah?

20:37.941 --> 20:39.879
Your sister
was my babysitter.

20:41.765 --> 20:43.926
And she used to have me
put makeup on her

20:44.246 --> 20:45.464
and, like,
feather her hair.

20:46.621 --> 20:48.080
Do you remember that look?

20:52.973 --> 20:54.496
What do you want?

20:57.777 --> 21:00.676
You made my brother look like
something he's not.

21:00.873 --> 21:01.887
Yeah?

21:02.273 --> 21:04.108
Look, I know
you won't take money.

21:04.480 --> 21:05.490
I've got a feeling

21:05.578 --> 21:07.705
you're not a man who
gives a shit about threats.

21:10.925 --> 21:12.754
I guess I was just hoping.

